verses.verse: יְהוָ֣ה <S%H3068><s%> Yah-weh The LORD מָלָךְ֮ <S%H4427><s%> ma-loCh reigneth גֵּא֪וּת <S%H1348><s%> ge-'Ut with majesty לָ֫בֵ֥שׁ <S%H3847><s%> la-Vesh he is clothed לָבֵ֣שׁ <S%H3847><s%> la-Vesh is clothed יְ֭הוָה <S%H3068><s%> Yah-weh the LORD עֹ֣ז <S%H5797><s%> 'oz with strength הִתְאַזָּ֑ר <S%H247><s%> hit-'az-Zar; [wherewith] he hath girded אַף־ <S%H637><s%> 'af- Indeed תִּכּ֥וֹן <S%H3559><s%> tik-Kon also is stablished תֵּ֝בֵ֗ל <S%H8398><s%> te-Vel, himself the world בַּל־ <S%H1077><s%> bal- lest תִּמּֽוֹט׃ <S%H4131><s%> tim-Mot. that it cannot be moved

נָכ֣וֹן <S%H3559><s%> na-Chon [is] established כִּסְאֲךָ֣ <S%H3678><s%> kis-'a-Cha Thy throne מֵאָ֑ז <S%H227><s%> me-'Az; of old מֵֽעוֹלָ֣ם <S%H5769><s%> me-'o-Lam thou [art] from everlasting אָֽתָּה׃ <S%H859><s%> 'At-tah. you

נָשְׂא֤וּ <S%H5375><s%> na-se-'U have lifted up נְהָר֨וֹת׀ <S%H5104><s%> ne-ha-Rot The floods יְֽהוָ֗ה <S%H3068><s%> Yah-weh O LORD נָשְׂא֣וּ <S%H5375><s%> na-se-'U have lifted up נְהָר֣וֹת <S%H5104><s%> ne-ha-Rot the floods קוֹלָ֑ם <S%H6963><s%> ko-Lam; their voice יִשְׂא֖וּ <S%H5375><s%> yis-'U lift up נְהָר֣וֹת <S%H5104><s%> ne-ha-Rot the floods דָּכְיָֽם׃ <S%H1796><s%> da-che-Yam. their waves

מִקֹּל֨וֹת׀ <S%H6963><s%> mik-ko-Lot than the noise מַ֤יִם <S%H4325><s%> Ma-yim waters רַבִּ֗ים <S%H7227><s%> rab-Bim, of many אַדִּירִ֣ים <S%H117><s%> 'ad-di-Rim [is] mightier מִשְׁבְּרֵי־ <S%H4867><s%> mish-be-rei- waves יָ֑ם <S%H3220><s%> Yam; of the sea אַדִּ֖יר <S%H117><s%> 'ad-Dir [yea than] the mighty בַּמָּר֣וֹם <S%H4791><s%> bam-ma-Rom on high יְהוָֽה׃ <S%H3068><s%> Yah-weh. The LORD

עֵֽדֹתֶ֨יךָ׀ <S%H5713><s%> 'e-do-Tei-cha Thy testimonies נֶאֶמְנ֬וּ <S%H539><s%> ne-'em-Nu sure מְאֹ֗ד <S%H3966><s%> me-'Od, are very לְבֵיתְךָ֥ <S%H1004><s%> le-vei-te-Cha thine house נַאֲוָה־ <S%H4998><s%> na-'a-vah- becometh קֹ֑דֶשׁ <S%H6944><s%> Ko-desh; holiness יְ֝הוָ֗ה <S%H3068><s%> Yah-weh O LORD לְאֹ֣רֶךְ <S%H753><s%> le-'O-rech forever יָמִֽים׃ <S%H3117><s%> ya-Mim. age
